OL,7,F"The guidance does not seek to direct
OL,8,FSafety Officers on the decisions to be
OL,9,Fmade as these will need to be dynamic
OL,10,Frisk-based decisions, but it outlines
OL,11,Fthe plans and briefings that should be
OL,12,Fin place before and during the match
OL,13,Fto help support the decision-making
OL,14,Fprocess."
OL,16,F"The guidance is reviewed and updated
OL,17,Fas necessary in partnership with the
OL,18,Fother relevant footballing bodies."
OL,20,FSheffield City Council have also been
OL,21,Fapproached for comment.
